title: Unsewered Communities, Iowa, 2007
name: Unsewered Communities, Iowa, 2007
description:
Abstract:
    The unsewered communities file was originally conceived as a representation of communities without a municipal sewer system or on-site septic systems. 
Purpose:
    The dataset was developed to assist the Unsewered Community Task Force in prioritizing communities to receive loans to fund the upgrade or installation of sewer/septic systems.

    This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.
